This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on January 16, 2013, titled "Engaging in Public Health Research on the Causes and Prevention of Gun Violence." The memorandum acknowledges that gun violence is not only a law enforcement challenge but also a serious public health issue that affects individuals, families, and communities across the United States. It emphasizes the need for a comprehensive approach to address this issue and states that a broader public health perspective is crucial. The memorandum directs the Secretary of Health and Human Services to conduct or sponsor research into the causes of gun violence and ways to prevent it. It also instructs the Secretary to identify pressing research questions and assess existing public health interventions for preventing gun violence. The memorandum includes general provisions that clarify its implementation and states that it does not create any substantive or procedural rights enforceable by any party against the United States or its entities. The memorandum concludes by authorizing the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register.